SIMPLE: estimation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Estimation
<hw>Es`ti*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aestimatio</ets>, fr. <ets>aestimare</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>estimation</ets>. See <er>Esteem</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of estimating.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An opinion or judgment of the worth, extent, or
quantity of anything, formed without using precise data; valuation;
<as>as, <ex>estimations</ex> of distance, magnitude, amount, or moral
qualities</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If he be poorer that thy <qex>estimation</qex>, then he shall
present himself before the priest, and the priest, and the priest shall
value him.</q> <rj><qau>Lev. xxvii. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Favorable opinion; esteem; regard; honor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I shall have <qex>estimation</qex> among multitude, and honor with
the elders.</q> <rj><qau>Wisdom viii. 10.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Supposition; conjecture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I speak not this in <qex>estimation</qex>,⟦br⟧
As what I think might be, but what I know.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Estimate; calculation; computation; appraisement;
esteem; honor; regard. See <er>Estimate</er>, <pos>n.</pos></syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Estimative</ent>⟦br⟧
